# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NDM Playwright UI Tests — Environment Configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values.
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The .env file is gitignored and loaded automatically when
# you run any test command (npm run test:live, etc.)
#
# By default, values point at the local Docker Compose setup
# (ndm-docker-compose). To run against a remote CP, override
# BASE_URL and auth variables with your deployment details.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Control Plane & Authentication ──────────────────────────
# Local Docker:  http://localhost:3111  (UI via Docker Compose)
# Remote CP:     https://<cp-ip>        (e.g. https://172.30.205.220)
BASE_URL=http://localhost:3111
NDM_TEST_USER=admin@datamigrator.local
NDM_TEST_PASSWORD=welcome

# ─── File Server / Discovery tests ──────────────────────────
# These require real infrastructure (workers + source filer).
# Smoke tests work without these variables.
# Uncomment and fill in to run discovery tests against a real filer.
#
# SOURCE_HOST=10.192.7.105
# PROTOCOL=NFS
# PROTOCOL_USERNAME=root
# PROTOCOL_PASSWORD=

# ─── Optional: Export paths for single-path discovery test ────
# Comma-separated. Omit to skip single-path tests (select-all still runs).
# EXPORT_PATHS=/ifs/exampleexport
